minimal_total_margin.description: minimal_total_margin == total margin_x == requested_total_margins_x. total margins ratio for x axiss (physical + virtual), with respect to input image size and represent sum of both sides. If physical margins are not sufficient, virtual margins will be used to get to the minimal_total_margin.
minimal_total_margin.additional_notes: Constant: no dynamic configuration even when control variable change.

requested_total_margins_y_fhd_30.description: Requested total margins ratio for y axis, with respect to input image size and represent sum of both sides. This is used for requesting physical margins and also to be sent to GeoLib. Actual y margins would be between [minimal_total_margin, requested_total_margins_y].
requested_total_margins_y_fhd_30.additional_notes: Constant: no dynamic configuration even when control variable change.

s3d_offset.additional_notes: Constant: no dynamic configuration even when control variable change.

ois_offset.additional_notes: Constant: no dynamic configuration even when control variable change.

acc_offset.additional_notes: Constant: no dynamic configuration even when control variable change.

enable.additional_notes: Constant: no dynamic configuration even when control variable change.

min_strength.description: Minimal stabilization strength for strong blur ( estimated_blur is greater than or equal to end_decrease_at_blur ).
min_strength.additional_notes: Constant: no dynamic configuration even when control variable change.

exposure_time_th.description: if (exp_time is greater than exposure_time_th) then blur masking feature is enabled. Otherwise disabled. Units are seconds.
exposure_time_th.additional_notes: Constant: no dynamic configuration even when control variable change.

start_decrease_at_blur.description: Blur below this point won't decrease strength. Units are pixels out of 1920 resolutions. Blur above this point will cause min_strength stabilization (in between start/end interpolate) Units are pixels out of 1920 resolutions. If (end_decrease_at_bluris greater thanstart_decrease_at_blur) then feature will be disabled.
start_decrease_at_blur.additional_notes: Constant: no dynamic configuration even when control variable change.

end_decrease_at_blur.description: Blur below this point won't decrease strength. Units are pixels out of 1920 resolutions. Blur above this point will cause min_strength stabilization (in between start/end interpolate) Units are pixels out of 1920 resolutions. If (end_decrease_at_bluris greater thanstart_decrease_at_blur) then feature will be disabled.
end_decrease_at_blur.additional_notes: Constant: no dynamic configuration even when control variable change.

pan_min_threshold.description: Threshold for pan detection on the filter result [rad/sec]. Lower than pan_min_threshold is not a pan. Higher than pan_max_threshold is a full pan. In between the weight is linear. Blur masking mechanism is only active when no pan is detected.
pan_min_threshold.additional_notes: Constant: no dynamic configuration even when control variable change.

pan_max_threshold.description: Threshold for pan detection on the filter result [rad/sec]. Lower than pan_min_threshold is not a pan. Higher than pan_max_threshold is a full pan. In between the weight is linear. Blur masking mechanism is only active when no pan is detected.
pan_max_threshold.additional_notes: Constant: no dynamic configuration even when control variable change.

blur_masking_res1.additional_notes: Constant: no dynamic configuration even when control variable change.

blur_masking_res2.additional_notes: Constant: no dynamic configuration even when control variable change.

ldc_grid_source.description: 0 = use grids defined here (local grid, only if ldc_grid_enable == 1, , otherwise no LDC). 1 = use grids defined in ICA/LDC Chromatix (only if its valid, otherwise no LDC). Comment: Usually take grids from ICA Chromatix unless the input FOV is different between Video with EIS or video without EIS. Or if the chip doesn't contains ICA Chromatix.
ldc_grid_source.additional_notes: Constant: no dynamic configuration even when control variable change.

ldc_grid_enable.description: Enable/validity for the grids below (defined under EIS Chromatix).
ldc_grid_enable.additional_notes: Constant: no dynamic configuration even when control variable change.

ldc_calib_domain.description: 0 = Invalid configuration for EIS local grid ( in ICA Chromatix it is calibration on full sensor FOV ). 1 = EIS local grid is calibrated on IFE Input @ DZ X1 domain (FOV). 2 = EIS local grid is calibrated on IFE Output @ DZ X1 domain (FOV). Comment: EIS local grid means the grid defined below and not the one coming from ICA Chromatix.
ldc_calib_domain.additional_notes: Constant: no dynamic configuration even when control variable change.

distorted_input_to_undistorted_ldc_grid_.description: LDC grid in2out. Grid is defined on IFE output at digital zoom X1. FOV includes the EIS margins (image could be 4:3 or any different ratio than 16:9).
distorted_input_to_undistorted_ldc_grid_.additional_notes: Constant: no dynamic configuration even when control variable change.

distorted_input_to_undistorted_ldc_grid_.description: Precision of the LDC in2out grid. 0: 35x27 samples (945 samples are used). 1: 67x51 samples (3417 samples are used).

ldc_model_type.description: 0 = custom/no model (grid is not by any of the following models model ), 1 = regular, 2= fisheye, 3 = reserved for a new model.

model_parameters_tab.description: Model parameters to be used with the selected model. Parameters interpretation per model:. For model 1: [k1 k2 p1 p2 k3]. For model 2: [k1 k2 k3 k4].
